parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request. You can use the client to generate the value, but you must ensure that it is unique among different requests.

The ClientToken value can contain only ASCII characters and cannot exceed 64 characters in length. For more information, see [How do I ensure idempotence ](~~25693~~).

parameters.name: DbscId
parameters.description: The ID of the dedicated block storage cluster.

parameters.name: Period
parameters.description: The time interval (seconds) between data retrieval points.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description: The region ID of the dedicated block storage cluster.
